%3ELow-income%20mothers%20based%20in%20Texas%20can%20now%20get%20postpartum%20care%20for%20a%20full%20year%20after%20childbirth.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20bill%20adds%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20postpartum%20support%20and%20could%20help%20lower%20maternal%20mortality%20rates.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20bill%20comes%20as%20maternal%20mortality%20rates%20in%20the%20US%20jumped%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnchs%2Fdata%2Fhestat%2Fmaternal-mortality%2F2021%2Fmaternal-mortality-rates-2021.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1%2C205%20women%20in%202021%20%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20754%20in%202019.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELow-income%20moms%20in%20Texas%20can%20now%20receive%20postpartum%20care%20for%20a%20full%20year%20after%20childbirth%20thanks%20to%20a%20new%20policy%20that%20increases%20access%20to%20medical%20services%20and%20mental%20health%20support%20for%20nearly%20140%2C000%20people%20in%20the%20next%20two%20years%2C%20policymakers%20predict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoms-postpartum-what-they-wish-their-partners-knew-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20mothers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20state%20were%20previously%20eligible%20for%20Medicaid%20for%20only%20two%20months%20following%20childbirth.%20The%20expansion%20bill%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20approved%20in%20January%20and%20will%20take%20effect%20on%20March%201%20%E2%80%94%20adds%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20statewide%20postpartum%20support%20and%20could%20help%20lower%20maternal%20mortality%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20bill%20comes%20as%20maternal%20mortality%20rates%20in%20the%20United%20States%20jumped%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnchs%2Fdata%2Fhestat%2Fmaternal-mortality%2F2021%2Fmaternal-mortality-rates-2021.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1%2C205%20women%20in%202021%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20the%20most%20recent%20year%20data%20is%20available%20%E2%80%94%20from%20754%20in%202019%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20half%20of%20nationwide%20maternal%20deaths%20occur%20in%20the%20year%20after%20childbirth%2C%20with%20Texas%20ranking%20among%20the%20most%20dangerous%20states%20for%20pregnant%20people%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dshs.texas.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Flegislative%2F2022-Reports%2F2022-MMMRC-DSHS-Joint-Biennial-Report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20from%20the%20Maternal%20Mortality%20and%20Morbidity%20Review%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Low-income%20women%20and%20women%20of%20color%20are%20especially%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program%20helps%20to%20mitigate%20healthcare%20burdens%20for%20low-income%20Americans%2C%20covering%20the%20cost%20of%20prenatal%20vitamins%2C%20labor%20and%20delivery%2C%20treatment%20for%20pregnancy%20complications%2C%20newborn%20checkups%2C%20support%20for%20perinatal%20depression%2C%20pharmaceutical%20fees%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kff.org%2Fmedicaid%2Fissue-brief%2Fwhat-does-the-recent-literature-say-about-medicaid-expansion-impacts-on-sexual-and-reproductive-health%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIncreased%20access%20to%20Medicaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20correlates%20with%20improved%20pre-pregnancy%20health%2C%20maternal%20health%2C%20and%20infant%20health%20outcomes%2C%20according%20to%20reports%20published%20in%202020%20and%202021%20by%20the%20KFF%2C%20formally%20known%20as%20the%20Kaiser%20Family%20Foundation.%20Low-income%20mothers%20are%20also%20significantly%20more%20likely%20to%20seek%20the%20prenatal%20and%20postpartum%20care%20they%20need%20when%20they%20have%20access%20to%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20qualifies%20for%20postpartum%20healthcare%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDiana%20Forester%2C%20director%20of%20health%20policy%20at%20the%20non-partisan%20policy%20organization%20Texans%20Care%20for%20Children%2C%20said%20the%20extension%20is%20a%20step%20to%20support%20healthy%20mothers%20and%20babies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDisagreements%20between%20elected%20officials%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%2C%20but%20this%20is%20an%20example%20of%20how%20our%20state%20legislators%20really%20can%20come%20together%20to%20improve%20access%20to%20healthcare%20for%20Texas%20families%2C%26quot%3B%20Forester%20said%20in%20a%20public%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnyone%20whose%20pregnancy%20ended%20in%20the%20months%20prior%20to%20March%202024%20will%20be%20eligible%20to%20re-enroll%20in%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20extended%20coverage%20is%20expected%20to%20cost%20%2485%20million%20by%20the%20end%20of%20fiscal%20year%202024%2C%20and%20a%20total%20of%20%24405%20million%20by%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Medicaid%20expansion%20proposal%20was%20previously%20denied%20by%20the%20federal%20government%20in%202021%2C%20citing%20that%20Texas'%20application%20used%20medically%20inaccurate%20language%20intended%20to%20exclude%20people%20who%20had%20abortions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20is%20now%20one%20of%2043%20states%20that%20have%20extended%20the%20window%20for%20postpartum%20healthcare%20coverage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-presidents-budget-fund-medicare-higher-taxes-lower-drug-prices-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunder%20Medicaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20half%20of%20births%20in%20Texas%20and%20across%20the%20country%20are%20financed%20by%20Medicaid.%20The%20monetary%20relief%20Texas%20mothers%20will%20receive%20depends%20on%20their%20specific%20income%20level%20and%20number%20of%20dependents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20lawmakers%20across%20the%20aisle%20supported%20the%20recent%20Medicaid%20expansion.%20But%20Senate%20Republicans%20advocated%20to%20include%20a%20%26quot%3Blegislative%20purpose%26quot%3B%20clause%20to%20ensure%20that%20individuals%20who%20have%20an%20elective%20abortion%20will%20not%20qualify%20for%20postpartum%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOut%20of%20the%20state's%20profound%20respect%20for%20the%20lives%20of%20mothers%20and%20unborn%20children%2C%20Medicaid%20coverage%20is%20extended%20for%20mothers%20whose%20pregnancies%20end%20in%20the%20delivery%20of%20the%20child%20or%20end%20in%20the%20natural%20loss%20of%20the%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Texas%20bill%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedicaid%20does%20not%20guarantee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F1-in-5-patients-travelled-out-state-abortion-care-early-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabortion%20coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20most%20states.%20And%20Texas%20has%20seen%20recent%20efforts%20to%20limit%20abortion%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhigh-risk-low-income-patients-abortion-more-expensive-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereproductive%20health%20care%20access%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20following%20the%20reversal%20of%20Roe%20v.%20Wade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20new%20mother%20supported%20by%20Medicaid%3F%20Have%20you%20faced%20challenges%20accessing%20pregnancy%20and%20postpartum%20healthcare%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aallisonkelly%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eallisonkelly%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-maternal-mortality-bill-new-mothers-pregnancy-postpartum-medicaid-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706211684000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b2b8fff4b446f3be9d1c79%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-maternal-mortality-bill-new-mothers-pregnancy-postpartum-medicaid-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20bill%20in%20Texas%20aims%20to%20lower%20the%20maternal%20mortalit