erve%20gears%20up%20for%20its%20first%20interest-rate%20cut%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%202019%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Thursday%20note%20from%20Ned%20Davis%20Research.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEd%20Clissold%2C%20chief%20US%20strategist%20at%20Ned%20Davis%20Research%2C%20crunched%20the%20numbers%20and%20found%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fdow_jones%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDow%20Jones%20Industrial%20Average%3C%2Fa%3E%20jumps%2015%25%20on%20average%20in%20the%20first%20year%20after%20the%20Fed's%20first%20interest%20rate%20cut.%20But%20those%20gains%20are%20even%20stronger%2C%20at%2024%25%2C%20when%20the%20interest%20rate%20cuts%20are%20coupled%20with%20no%20recession%20in%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22778%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22No%20recession%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b28fd9f4b446f3be9d1089%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22664%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ENed%20Davis%20Research%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Dow%20Jones%20Industrial%20Average%20has%20rallied%20more%20when%20a%20recession%20has%20not%20occurred%20within%20a%20year%20before%20or%20after%20the%20first%20cut%2C%26quot%3B%20Clissold%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20has%20signaled%20that%20it%20plans%20to%20cut%20interest%20rates%20at%20least%20three%20times%20this%20year%20after%20inflation%20has%20moderated%20considerably%20from%20its%20June%202022%20peak.%20Meanwhile%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-economy-gdp-fourth-quarter-of-2023-2024-1%23%3A~%3Atext%3DReal%2520GDP%2520grew%2520at%2520an%2Cpoint%2520suggests%2520still%2520strong%2520growth.%5C%22%3Esolid%20GDP%20growth%20and%20a%20resilient%20jobs%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20signaled%20to%20investors%20that%20a%20recession%20does%20not%20appear%20imminent%2C%20setting%20the%20stock%20market%2