p%20the%20symptoms%20of%20PCOS.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESupplements%20she%20recommends%20for%20PCOS%20include%20inositol%2C%20zinc%2C%20and%20cinnamon.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20ObGyn%20shared%20the%20supplements%20that%20she%20recommends%20to%20her%20patients%20to%20ease%20the%20symptoms%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fwhat-is-pcos%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epolycystic%20ovarian%20syndrome%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fpcos-symptoms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPCOS%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20hormonal%20disorder%20thought%20to%20affect%20between%20six%20to%2012%25%20of%20US%20women%2C%20where%20the%20ovaries%20produce%20unusually%20high%20levels%20of%20hormones%20called%20androgens%20(known%20as%20hyperandrogenism).%20People%20with%20PCOS%20may%20have%20small%20cysts%20on%20their%20ovaries%2C%20irregular%20periods%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Finsulin-resistance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einsulin%20resistance%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20excess%20hair%20growth%2C%20and%20infertility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20a%20person's%20symptoms%2C%20PCOS%20can%20be%20treated%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpcos-symptoms-mounjaro-ozempic-treatment-drugs-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emedications%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20encourage%20regular%20periods%2C%20block%20the%20effects%20of%20androgens%2C%20and%20%E2%80%94%20because%20insulin%20resistance%20can%20be%20a%20feature%20of%20the%20condition%20%E2%80%94%20help%20the%20body%20process%20insulin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20taking%20supplements%20can%20also%20%26quot%3Bdefinitely%20improve%26quot%3B%20people's%20daily%20experiences%20of%20PCOS%2C%20Dr.%20Fran%20Haydanek%2C%20an%20ObGyn%20who%20works%20at%20Rochester%20Regional%20Health%20in%20New%20York%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20PCOS%20patient%20doesn't%20have%20major%20concerns%20about%20their%20symptoms%20or%20wants%20to%20try%20to%20manage%20their%20symptoms%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fpcos-diet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elifestyle%20changes%3C%2Fu%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Eshe%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Erecommends%20supplements%20such%20as%20inositol%2C%20zinc%2C%20calcium%2C%20vitamin%20D%2C%20and%20spearmint.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhich%20supplements%20are%20most%20appropriate%20depends%20on%20the%20PCOS%20symptoms%20a%20patient%20has%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaydanek%20said%20that%20inositol%20%26quot%3Btreats%20underlying%20causes%26quot%3B%20of%20PCOS%2C%20while%20zinc%2C%20calcium%2C%20and%20vitamin%20D%20are%20more%20of%20an%20%26quot%3Badjunct%20to%20therapy%26quot%3B%20with%20evidence%20suggesting%20that%20they%20could%20help%20patients%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fwhen-do-you-ovulate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eovulate%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20have%20a%20higher%20chance%20of%20becoming%20ovulatory%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaydanek%20said%20to%20consult%20your%20doctor%20before%20taking%20supplements%20to%20ensure%20they're%20right%20for%20you%20and%20don't%20interact%20with%20any%20medications%20you're%20taking.%20If%20you%20try%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F5-supplements-for-longevity-and-anti-aging-expert-recommendations-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enew%20supplement%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20will%20take%20three%20to%20six%20months%20to%20see%20if%20it%20works%2C%20especially%20inositol%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EInositol%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaydanek%20said%20inositol%2C%20which%20is%20a%20type%20of%20sugar%20found%20in%20the%20body%2C%20is%20the%20main%20supplement%20she%20recommends%20to%20patients%20with%20PCOS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20imbalance%20of%20inositols%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epromotes%20insulin%20resistance%20and%20the%20production%20of%20androgens%2C%20which%20are%20two%20of%20the%20underlying%20mechanisms%20of%20how%20PCOS%20develops%2C%20Haydanek%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInositol%20supplements%20are%20thought%20to%20restore%20the%20correct%20ratio%20of%20inositols%20in%20the%20body%2C%20helping%20to%20reverse%20some%20of%20the%20signs%20and%20symptoms%20of%20PCOS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Fdrugs%2F25173-inositol%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAccording%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Cleveland%20Clinic%2C%20as%20well%20as%20improving%20blood%20sugar%20levels%2C%20inositol%20can%20reduce%20blood%20pressure%20and%20promote%20ovulation%20in%20people%20with%20PCOS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaydanek%20said%20that%20recent%20studies%20have%20suggested%20that%20inositol%20is%20as%20effective%20in%20treating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffaith-hill-daughter-gracie-mcgraw-takes-ozempic-mounjaro-for-pcos-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einsulin%20resistance%20in%20PCOS%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20patients%20as%20metformin%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bcurrent%20gold%20standard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECinnamon%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EClinical%20trials%20in%20people%20with%20PCOS%20suggest%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fcinnamon-benefits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecinnamon%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20reduce%20their%20insulin%20resistance%2C%20testosterone%20levels%2C%20and%20weight%2C%20as%20well%20as%20help%20regulate%20their%20menstrual%20cycles.%20A%202021%20review%20of%20studies%20found%20that%20the%20research%20on%20cinnamon's%20effects%20on%20the%20above%20symptoms%20of%20PCOS%20was%20%26quot%3Bpromising%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20that%20more%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20to%20know%20for%20sure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECalcium%20and%20vitamin%20D%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaydanek%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fvitamin-d-benefits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Evitamin%20D%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20calcium%20can%20help%20with%20PCOS%20symptoms%20as%20well%20as%20general%20health%2C%20as%20most%20people%20don't%20get%20enough%20vitamin%20D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202022%20review%20of%20studies%20concluded%20that%20calcium%20and%20vitamin%20D%20show%20promise%20for%20improving%20PCOS%20symptoms%20such%20as%20irregular%20periods%2C%20high%20testosterone%20levels%2C%20and%20hirsutism%20(excessive%20hair%20growth).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20review%20said%20that%20the%20findings%20of%20multiple%20studies%20suggest%20that%20these%20improvements%20aren't%20solely%20down%20to%20calcium%20and%20vitamin%20D%20supplementation%20%E2%80%94%20instead%2C%20they%20act%20in%20tandem%20with%20metformin%20and%20other%20micronutrients%20such%20as%20magnesium%2C%20zinc%2C%20vitamin%20K%2C%20and%20vitamin%20E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EZinc%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20suggests%20that%20zinc%20could%20help%20insulin%20resistance%20in%20women%20with%20PCOS%2C%20according%20to%20a%202020%20review%20of%20studies%2C%20but%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20it%20helps%20with%20hormonal%20balance.%20There's%20some%20limited%20evidence%20that%20it%20is%20an%20anti-androgen%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20affect%20the%20hirsutism%20that%20is%20a%20result%20of%20hyperandrogenism%20in%20people%20with%20PCOS%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20review%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESpearmint%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSpearmint%20has%20been%20shown%20to%20be%20helpful%20with%20some%20of%20the%20androgenic%20symptoms%20of%20PCOS%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%