0the%20%E2%80%9CIndian%20network%20of%20extra-judicial%20and%20extra-territorial%20killings%20has%20become%20a%20global%20phenomenon%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQazi%20said%20that%20investigation%20had%20found%20%E2%80%9Ccredible%20evidence%E2%80%9D%20linking%20Indian%20agents%2C%20identified%20as%20Yogesh%20Kumar%20and%20Ashok%20Kumar%20Anand%2C%20with%20the%20killing%20of%20Muhammad%20Riaz%20in%20September%202023%20and%20Shahid%20Latif%20in%20October%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20dismissed%20the%20Pakistani%20allegations.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20seen%20media%20reports%20regarding%20certain%20remarks%20by%20Pakistan%20Foreign%20Secretary.%20It%20is%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20latest%20attempt%20at%20peddling%20false%20and%20malicious%20anti-India%20propaganda%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fresponse-to-queries.htm%3Fdtl%2F37532%2FOfficial_Spokespersons_response_to_media_queries_regarding_remarks_made_by_Pakistan_Foreign_Ministry%5C%22%3Esaid%20MEA%20spokesperson%20Randhir%20Jaiswal%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20asserted%20that%20Pakistan%20has%20long%20been%20known%20worldwide%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20epicentre%20of%20terrorism%2C%20organised%20crime%2C%20and%20illegal%20transnational%20activities%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20and%20many%20other%20countries%20have%20publicly%20warned%20Pakistan%20cautioning%20that%20it%20would%20be%20consumed%20by%20its%20own%20culture%20of%20terror%20and%20violence.%20Pakistan%20will%20reap%20what%20it%20sows.%20To%20blame%20others%20for%20its%20own%20misdeeds%20can%20neither%20be%20a%20justification%20nor%20a%20solution%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20spokesperson.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pakistan%20foreign%20secretary%20alleged%20that%20Indian%20agents%20%E2%80%9Crecruited%2C%20financed%20and%20supported%20criminals%2C%20terrorists%20and%20unsuspecting%20civilians%20to%20play%20defined%20roles%20in%20these%20assassinations%E2%80%9D.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cevidence%E2%80%9D%20was%20confessions%20from%20the%20alleged%20hitmen%20and%20money%20transfers%20into%20their%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20Indian%20media%20and%20social%20media%20accounts%20promptly%20celebrated%20the%20killing%20of%20the%20two%20men%20as%20%E2%80%9Csuccessful%20retribution%20against%20enemies%20of%20India%20and%20projected%20their%20capacity%20to%20carry%20out%20these%20illegal%20acts%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Qazi%20referred%20to%20a%20Muhammad%20Riaz%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Findia-shahid-latif-hardeep-nijjar-terrorists-attacked-killed-pakistan-nepal-canada-2447590-2023-10-11%5C%22%3EIndian%20media%20had%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20September%20about%20the%20killing%20of%20Riyaz%20Ahmad%2C%20a%20Lashkar-e-Toiba%20member%2C%20at%20Rawalkot%20in%20September%202023.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Flatest%2Fworld%2Fstory%2Fpathankot-attack-mastermind-shahid-latif-shot-dead-by-unidentified-assailants-401506-2023-10-11%5C%22%3ELatif%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20member%20of%20Jaish-e-Mohhammed%20and%20described%20as%20a%20mastermind%20of%20the%20terror%20attack%20on%20the%20Pathankot%20air%20base%2C%20was%20gunned%20down%20in%20a%20mosque%20at%20Sialkot%20in%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQazi%20additionally%20connected%20the%20killings%20in%20Pakistan%20to%20a%20perceived%20pattern%20of%20purported%20actions%20by%20Indian%20agents%20in%20Canada%20and%20the%20US.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20killing%20of%20a%20Sikh%20leader%20in%20Canada%20is%20just%20one%20example%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20global%20operations%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20must%20be%20held%20accountable%20internationally%20for%20its%20blatant%20violation%20of%20international%20law.%20India%E2%80%99s%20assassination%20of%20Pakistani%20nationals%20on%20Pakistani%20soil%20is%20a%20violation%20of