Airlines%20said%20that%20it%20will%20receive%20six%20fewer%20new%20planes%20than%20it%20expected%20this%20year%20because%20of%20ongoing%20production%20problems%20at%20Boeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESouthwest%20has%20ordered%20more%20than%20300%20Boeing%20737%20Max%207%20jets%2C%20the%20smallest%20of%20the%20Max%20lineup%2C%20but%20Boeing%20is%20already%20behind%20schedule%20in%20gaining%20regulatory%20approval%20for%20the%20plane.%20That%20process%20will%20likely%20be%20pushed%20back%20even%20further%20by%20the%20safety%20concerns%20over%20the%20Max%209%20and%20Boeing's%20quality%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CEOs%20of%20Alaska%20and%20United%20blasted%20Boeing%20earlier%20this%20week.%20American%20Airlines%20CEO%20Robert%20Isom%20chimed%20in%20on%20Thursday%2C%20calling%20Boeing's%20safety%20issues%20%26quot%3Bunacceptable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoeing%20needs%20to%20get%20their%20act%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20on%20a%20call%20with%20analysts%20and%20reporters.%20%26quot%3BAll%20of%20Boeing%20needs%20to%20come%20together%20and%20to%20get%20back%20on%20the%20right%20track.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20financial%20side%2C%20American%20saw%20its%20profit%20drop%20sharply%20and%20forecast%20that%20it%20will%20lose%20money%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202024.%20Southwest%20Airlines%20reported%20a%20fourth-quarter%20loss.%20Both%20carriers%20are%20struggling%20to%20cover%20rising%20labor%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20earned%20%2419%20million%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%2C%20down%20from%20%24803%20million%20a%20year%20earlier.%20Excluding%20one-time%20items%2C%20mostly%20contract-ratification%20bonuses%20for%20pilots%2C%20the%20airline%20said%20adjusted%20profit%20was%2029%20cents%20per%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20expected%20American%20Airlines%20Group%20Inc.%20to%20earn%2011%20cents%20per%20share%2C%20according%20to%20a%20FactSet%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERevenue%20declined%201%25%2C%20to%20%2413.06%20billion%2C%20slightly